                    .heading Tips for Staying Active While Traveling
                    .content 
                        p Staying active while traveling can be challenging, but with some planning, you can maintain your fitness routine on the go.
                        h2 Strategies for Staying Active
                        p Here are some tips to help you stay active while traveling:
                        ul
                            li 
                                strong Plan Ahead:
                                |  Research fitness facilities or walking routes at your destination.
                            li 
                                strong Pack Portable Equipment:
                                |  Bring items like resistance bands or a jump rope for easy workouts.
                            li 
                                strong Incorporate Walking:
                                |  Walk as much as possible, whether exploring the city or getting to meetings.
                            li 
                                strong Use Hotel Gyms:
                                |  Take advantage of hotel gyms or fitness centers.
                            li 
                                strong Do Bodyweight Exercises:
                                |  Perform exercises that don’t require equipment, like push-ups and squats.
                        p By incorporating these strategies, you can stay active and maintain your fitness routine while traveling.
                .article 
                    .heading Understanding Macronutrients: Protein, Carbs, and Fats
                    .content 
                        p Macronutrients—protein, carbohydrates, and fats—are essential for fueling your body and supporting your fitness goals.
                        h2 The Role of Macronutrients
                        p Here’s how each macronutrient contributes to your health:
                        ul
                            li 
                                strong Protein:
                                |  Essential for muscle repair and growth, protein should be a key part of your diet.
                            li 
                                strong Carbohydrates:
                                |  Provide energy for physical activity and support brain function.
                            li 
                                strong Fats:
                                |  Necessary for hormone production, brain health, and energy storage.
                        p A balanced diet includes an appropriate mix of these macronutrients to support your fitness and health.
